Running tests

First Copy the <WSFPHP>\samples directory and <WSFPHP>\src\test\samples\services directory to your web servers document root.

Then

1. Set TEST_PHP_EXECUTABLE variable to point to the php executable.
2. Following command will execute the tests in the samples directory.

php run-tests.php samples

Using pear tool
----------------
To run the tests use command
pear run-tests -r samples  {-r flag is for running the tests in directories as well.}


